<p>Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&acute;s comprehensive Life Management programs are designed to assist employees with many of life's challenges and opportunities:</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Adoption Reimbursement</H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">Reimburses up to $8,000 per adopted child upon legal adoption for eligible employees.</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Child Care Plus<span style="font-size: 0.8em; position: relative; top: -0.6em;">&reg;</span></H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">Eligible employees can enroll in Child Care Plus, which helps pay for child care expenses incurred while working. Eligible employees can receive up to $240 per month, per child under 5 years of age or up to $205 per month, per child age 5 to under age 13 (under 21, if incapable of self-care). Care can be provided through a licensed facility (like a child care center) or an informal type of care (like a babysitter).</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Tuition Reimbursement</H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">The bank reimburses eligible employees up to $5,250 for job-related courses or to fulfill a job-related degree program.</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">LifeCare<span style="font-size: 0.8em; position: relative; top: -0.6em;">&reg;</span></H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">A free, confidential resource and referral program offering practical advice and support to help employees  and their families manage work and personal responsibilities, including financial and parenting advice and help finding child- and elder-care resources.</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Employee Assistance Program (EAP)</H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">A voluntary, confidential service to help employees and their family deal with family problems, job-related issues, stress and other situations.</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">
<a href="<%Response.write href_pre%>flexible_wa.asp" class="bacb" title="Flexible Work Arrangements">Flexible Work Arrangements</a></H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America offers multiple ways for employees and managers to define when and where employees work, including flex-time, telecommuting, compressed work schedules and job sharing. With the My Work<span style="font-size: 0.8em; position: relative; top: -0.6em;">&reg;</span> program, employees have the opportunity to work from a variety of corporate bank locations or from home instead of a traditional, dedicated cube or office.</p>


<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Auto and Home Insurance</H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">Provides employees with special group rates on a variety of insurance policies, including those for homes, condominiums, autos, recreational vehicles and rental homes.</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">Commuter Benefit Program</H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">Enables employees to pay for eligible work-related commuting expenses, like mass transit or parking, with pretax dollars (up to the IRS limit). Parking expenses eligible in all areas except the state of Washington.</p>

<H2 class="bac" style="margin: 12px 0px 0px 0px; padding: 0px;">
<a href="<%Response.write href_pre%>timeoff.asp" class="bacb" title="Time Away">Time Away</a></H2>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;">Offers employees a range of paid and unpaid leave options for taking the time they need away from work for vacation, health and family issues, and a range of other personal needs.</p>

